                <h1>Make Your Picture Transparent in PowerPoint: Easy Steps</h1>
                <p>To make a picture transparent in PowerPoint, first select the image you want to modify. Go to the "Format" tab and click on "Transparency" in the Adjust group. Choose a preset transparency level or click on "Picture Transparency Options" for a custom setting. Adjust the slider and apply the changes to see your image become see-through!</p>
